Free Coding Bootcamps: The Best No-Cost Codi= ng Programs

<= div class=3D"">
Joshua Weinstein
Jun 18, 2020
1

Codi= ng bootcamps are the new face of education. They stand to revolutionize= career training schools for decades to come. Coding bootcamps, unlike coll= ege, train students for a career in the tech industry with computer program= ming. This direct-training approach is unique to coding bootcamps.

Th= ese short-term programs usually last between 6 weeks and 6 months. Bootcamp= s are a proven way to increase your salary and improve your career prospect= s. With programs like income share agreements and living stipends, they=E2= =80=99re more affordable than ever.

Unfortunately, even cheap coding = bootcamps can still carry a hefty price tag. This means it=E2=80=99s someti= mes difficult to commit because of cost. Thankfully, there=E2=80=99s anothe= r option for those that want to learn to code for free.

Free coding s= chools are a no-cost alternative. They provide many of the same benefits as= a paid program. Free coding programs are a great introduction to programmi= ng. Plus the majority of these programs are held via an online learning pla= tform, so they=E2=80=99re accessible from everywhere.

Take this qui= z to get offers and scholarships from top bootcamps and online schools!=

See your matches

So, what ar= e the best free coding bootcamps, and what courses do they offer? In this a= rticle, we=E2=80=99ll go over the best free coding websites and bootcamps s= o you can decide what class is best for you.

42

42 School originated i= n France, and is one of the largest in-person free coding bootcamps around.= Recently, the program moved to a new location in Silicon Valley. To enter = the program, students begin by completing an around-the-clock coding challe= nge called a =E2=80=98Piscene.=E2=80=99 Students who pass the test are admi= tted into the program, which is self-paced. The location features dormitori= es and a cafeteria, where meals are sold at cost of production.

Ada Developers Aca= demy

This Seattle-based bootcamp offers immersi= ve programming courses to local students. Ada Developers Academy offers a f= ull stack web development course. The course runs 27 weeks. Furthermore, th= e program is free to women and non-binary students.

App Academy Open
App Academy Open. This online program gives = students access to the complete App Academy full stack web development curr= iculum. It includes over 1,500 hours of course materials and resources. App= Academy is a well-known bootcamp, and the free program contains the same c= oursework that made it famous.

Bento.io

Bento.io takes an interesting approach to free courses = in coding and web development. Each =E2=80=9Ctrack=E2=80=9D is a mini-cours= e compiled from learning resources from around the web. It=E2=80=99s a grea= t approach that allows you to learn in different ways and from many differe= nt sources. Bento offers tracks in CSS, HTML, JavaScript, Git, Python, jQue= ry, and more. It also has more comprehensive tracks like those for front en= d development, backend development, and web fundamentals.

Bridge

Bridge is a women=E2=80=99s coding bo= otcamp that offers an 11-week software development course. Students work on= a wide range of portfolio projects. These projects are designed to impart = real-world experience. This women=E2=80=99s bootcamp helps build technical = skills. It offers a supportive and high-tech environment. Bridge is an in-p= erson bootcamp, offering classes 2 times per week. The instructors are indu= stry experts.

Codecademy
 

CodeCademy is a well-known free bootcamp. This online program is popu= lar with beginners and intermediate coders. Students learn coding languages= like HTML and JavaScript. Students work on projects to improve their skill= s and build a portfolio. CodeCademy=E2=80=99s free courses offer a chance t= o learn programming at no cost.

=C2=BB MORE:  Three Best Web D= eveloper Bootcamps

Codewars

Codewars is an outstanding and innovative way to learn how to code. T= he program involves challenges, which they call =E2=80=9Ckata=E2=80=9D, in = which you code with other users to learn programming languages like Java, J= avaScript, Python, Ruby, and many others.

Coursera

Coursera is a unique free coding bootcamp. Classes at this bootcamp a= re taught by university professors. And while the courses are free, there a= re some small charges involved. This popular bootcamp offers certificates, = which cost between around $30 and $50. The certificates verify course compl= etion and make a welcome addition to a portfolio.

The Data Incubator

The Data Incubat= or offers a free coding bootcamp for experienced programmers. The curriculu= m is designed to equip these individuals with the final important skills to= become true seasoned professionals. The program is a fellowship, free for = students. Employers pay a fee if they hire a fellow.

edX

edX, like Cour= sera, offers hundreds of massive open online courses (MOOCs) on every subje= ct under the sun. But their tech courses are especially great. On edX, you = can take free courses in HTML5, CSS, mobile application development, Java P= rogramming, and much more=E2=80=93all from top university instructors.

<= h3>Flat= iron School Introductory Courses

Flatiron School is a big-name coding boo= tcamp. With locations in London, New York City, and Washington D.C., studen= ts can attend programming courses in-person or online. And their introductory courses= are completely free.

Founders & Coders

Founders and Coders holds the= title of being the first free coding bootcamp in the United Kingdom. It of= fers beginner-friendly courses in full stack web development and covers a r= ange of common coding languages.

Free Code Camp

Free Code Camp offers coding certificates in = front end and full stack development. This online program is self-paced and= offers a 1,600-hour JavaScript curriculum. Demographically, Free Code Camp= stands out. Roughly 80% of its coding community is over 25 years old, and = 20% of its students are women.

Fullstack Academy Prep Program
 

Ful= lstack Academy offers a free introductory preparation coding bootcamp. The = program covers full stack JavaScript over a period of 13 weeks, and helps s= tudents gain the foundation they need to be successful in coding. Courses a= re available in New York City and Chicago.

GA Dash

General Assembly offers a free coding bootcamp called GA Dash. This program is project-based. For = example, students build an entire Tumblr theme from the ground-up. This uni= que program is popular, and comes from a top paid coding bootcamp.

<= span class=3D"ez-toc-section" id=3D"hack-reactor-basic-prep">Hack Reactor Basic Prep<= br>

Hack Re= actor, a well-known coding bootcamp, offers a free program called Hack Reac= tor Basic Prep. Th= e course is as it sounds=E2=80=94an introductory course designed for beginn= ers. The program runs for 12 weeks and covers all the basics of coding.

=

Hackr.io
=

While Hackr.io isn=E2=80=99t itself a free coding bootcamp, it is s= till a fantastic free resource for anyone wanting to teach themselves to co= de. The site offers fairly comprehensive listings of online courses and tut= orials, broken down by coding languages and topics. Definitely one to bookm= ark!

Insigh= t Data Science

Insight D= ata Science offers a free post-doctoral coding bootcamp, which helps high-l= evel graduates learn valuable data science skills. The program runs for sev= en weeks in Boston, New York City, Seattle, and Silicon Valley. There=E2=80= =99s also a remote program available for students outside of those specific= locations.

Kenzie Free

Kenzie Free is a no-cost introductory coding = bootcamp for beginners. Kenzie Academy=E2=80=99s new free and self-paced pr= ogram is available online. Kenzie Free allows potential programmers to lear= n from a top tier bootcamp without any financial commitments. Kenzie Free c= overs the basics of HTML, CSS, and later offers an introduction to JavaScri= pt. Kenzie Academy=E2=80=99s mini-courses allow anyone interested in coding= to get a feel for the subject, learn practical skills, and decide if they = want to pursue a career in tech=E2=80=94all for free.

=C2=BB MORE:  The Best Game Development Bootcamps of 2019
=

Khan Academy

Khan Academy courses are very popular. They=E2=80=99r= e not a coding bootcamp, but this free education source offers a long list = of free coding courses. Students can sharpen their computer skills with Kha= n Academy, and learn a lot on the way.

Makers Academy

Makers Academy is a UK-based coding boot= camp offering software development training. Makers Academy has a junior de= velopment job offer guarantee, which students receive at the end of the 12-= week program.

MIT OpenCourseware

One of the most prestigi= ous technical universities in the world, MIT has decided to offer many of i= ts renowned computer science programs to the public completely free. Among = their many complete courses are Introduction to Computer Science and Progra= mming, Introduction to Programming in Python, Artificial Intelligence, Prog= ramming for the Puzzled, and Advanced Data Structures.

NodeSchool

NodeSchool is a free coding bootcamp off= ering a range of useful tutorials and courses. The program is open-source a= nd run by volunteers, and aims to provide the best way to learn coding. The= program is entirely tuition-free to anyone who enrolls.

The Odin Project

The Odin Project was designe= d to train new coders from the ground-up. The program offers free tech care= er training courses in web development. Students start with an introductory= course, then move on to web development 101. The course curriculum include= s HTML, CSS, Ruby, Rails, Git, and more. The Odin Project offers flexible t= utorials and lessons. This coding bootcamp is a great place for beginners t= o start, and offers excellent resources across the board.

Recurse Center

Recurse Center is a = New York-based free coding bootcamp that offers an immersive in-person prog= ram. The bootcamp runs for 3 months, and offers a chance for individuals to= sharpen their coding skills. Admissions information and course dates are a= vailable online.

Re= silient Coders

Resilient Coders offers a full-time JavaScript bootcamp in= Boston, Massachusetts. This program is for people of color trying to enter= the tech industry. The 14-week course covers a range of coding languages i= ncluding HTML, CSS, JavaScript, and more. After graduation, students will b= e proficient coders, and ready to launch a career.

Revature

Revature works by partnering with universities to offer free codin= g classes to students. Some courses are in-person, and some are online. Imm= ersive courses cover programming and software development. The program can = help students bolster their university education with real, practical devel= opment and coding skills.

Revolent

While Revolent isn=E2=80=99t technica= lly a coding bootcamp, it does offer short-term tech education programs. Re= volent provides free, quality courses that prepare students to become certi= fied Salesforce developers, administrators, and consultants. There is also = a course that trains candidates to become certified ServiceNow consultants.= Revolent courses last 10-12 weeks in New York, London, Melbourn, and Amste= rdam. During the program, students are assigned a mentor to support them th= roughout the course, and, upon completion of the certificate, students begi= n working with one of Revolent=E2=80=99s tech company partners for two year= s.

Rithm School

Rithm School offers a= fast-paced 4-month full stack development program. During the program, stu= dents focus on JavaScript and Python. Students have the opportunity to part= icipate in a variety of open-source projects and portfolio-building activit= ies.

RMOTR

RMOTR offers an online coding bootcamp with in= teractive lessons and projects. During the 4-month program, students will l= earn a variety of coding languages and participate in portfolio-building pr= ojects. Live support is part of the program, and RMOTR emphasizes student p= rojects and participation.

Sabio

Sabio currently offers a free PreWork cou= rse in Front End Web Development. The course includes videos, tests, access= to a Slack Team, and even live office hours with your instructors. Sabio= =E2=80=99s free course covers topics like HTML, CSS, JavaScript, Bootstrap,= and much more=E2=80=93all for free!

<= /div>

Scotch.io

Scotch.io is a large compe= ndium of free, text-based programming courses. It=E2=80=99s a fantastic res= ource for those who prefer to learn by reading, rather than by watching vid= eos. Among the courses offered by Scotch are React, JavaScript, jQuery, and= Vue.

Skillcrush=E2=80=99s Free Coding Bootcamp

SkillCrush offers free technology = and coding courses to anyone interested in tech. From aspiring software eng= ineers to complete beginners, SkillCrush offers something useful to learn. = Students can learn coding languages like Java, Python, HTML, and JavaScript= using Skillcrush lessons.

SoloLearn

SoloLearn offers a series of interactive cod= ing courses through their online platform. It offers short and clever tutor= ials on just about every programming language you could ask for, including,= Python, Java, C++, JavaScript, C#, PHP, Ruby, Swift, jQuery, C, HTML, CSS,= and SQL.

Udacity

Udacity offers coding courses for beginners and inte= rmediate programmers. Udacity offers special =E2=80=98nano degrees=E2=80=99= in specific topics like web development and data analytics. And while the = courses are free, the nano degrees do come with a small price. Udacity stud= ents can use their skills to get a job in tech, or pursue further education= .

Udemy

<= p>Udemy offers paid and free online coding courses. Students can learn a sp= ecific programming language or take another program like web development or= data science. Udemy offers an open-platform for anyone to create technolog= y courses, so use discretion when selecting a class.

w3schools
=

w3schools is another fantastic site that offers comprehensive t= ext-based tutorials and courses on HTML, CSS, JavaScript, XML, SQL, PHP, Re= act, jQuery, and much more. Another great benefit of w3schools is the quizz= es integrated into the courses to check your learning progress. While w3sch= ools courses are completely free, you also have the option of paying for a = certification, even after you=E2=80=99ve completed a free course.

Finding the Right Coding Bootcamp for You with Career Karma<= /h2>

While this i= s not a complete list, it covers the best of the cheapest coding bootcamps.= So with all the amazing options, how do you choose the right free coding b= ootcamp? You have to ask yourself a few questions to find the best coding c= lasses for you. 

What are you looking for in a bootcamp? Do you = have a specific vision or goal in mind, or are you looking for a primer? Do= you want to work as a developer full-time or do you want it to be a skill = to complement other skills you already have? Front end or back end? What pr= ogramming languages do you want to learn? How much time do you have? How mu= ch are you able to learn on your own? Do you want to learn in-person, or do= you like online courses?

These questions will help you get a clearer= sense of which bootcamps to look towards. Download the free Career Karma app and get help answering these qu= estions.

Free Coding Bootcamp FAQ

=F0=9F=92=BC Will a fre= e coding bootcamp help me get a job?

Maybe, but it depends on the program. Most free bootcamps offer introducto= ry classes or language-specific tutorials. If you=E2=80=99re ready for job = training, consider a paid bootcamp.

= =E2=AD=90 What are free coding bootcamps good for?

Free coding bootcamps are great for learning coding language= s and getting a sense of what it=E2=80=99s like to be a programmer. Many fr= ee bootcamps serve as excellent coding bootcamp prep programs.

=F0=9F=8F=AB Are there any in-person free coding boot= camps?

Yes, programs like 42 offer courses on-location, but= most free bootcamps are online.
